# B2B Engineering Team Management TODO

## Phase 1 - Delivery Workflow Foundation

- [ ] Add custom workflow states
  - Backend: create `apps/backend/src/models/workflow.model.ts`
  - Backend: create workflow routes/controllers/services under `/workflow`
  - Scope states by `workspace` and optional `project`
  - Support ordered states, category (`BACKLOG`, `TODO`, `IN_PROGRESS`, `REVIEW`, `DONE`), color, and `isDefault`
  - Update task validation so status must match the workspace/project workflow
  - Migration/seed: create default workflow from current task statuses

- [ ] Add backlog ordering
  - Backend: add `rank` or `sortOrder` to `TaskModel`
  - API: reorder tasks within workspace/project/sprint
  - API: list backlog tasks where `sprint: null`
  - Rules: preserve order when moving tasks into and out of sprints

- [ ] Add epics
  - Backend: create `EpicModel` with `name`, `description`, `status`, `project`, `workspace`, `owner`, `startDate`, `targetDate`
  - Backend: add optional `epic` reference to `TaskModel`
  - API: CRUD epics, list epic tasks, epic progress analytics
  - UI follow-up: epic detail view and epic filter in task list

## Phase 2 - GitHub-Centered Engineering Flow

- [ ] Link GitHub commits and pull requests to tasks
  - Backend: extend `IntegrationModel` or add `RepositoryIntegrationModel`
  - Backend: add `PullRequestModel` with PR number, title, URL, branch, author, status, mergedAt, task references
  - Webhook: parse task codes from branch names, PR titles, commit messages, and descriptions
  - API: list PRs linked to a task/project
  - Notifications: notify assignee when PR opens, review requested, merged, or CI fails

- [ ] Add branch and task automation
  - API: generate branch names from task code and title, e.g. `feature/TSK-123-add-billing-filter`
  - Automation: move task to review when PR opens
  - Automation: move task to done when PR merges, if configured
  - Safety: require workspace-level settings before auto-closing tasks

- [ ] Add deployment tracking
  - Backend: create `DeploymentModel` with provider, environment, status, commitSha, release, startedAt, completedAt
  - Webhook: support deploy success/failure events
  - API: show deployments by project, release, and linked task

## Phase 3 - Planning, Releases, and Capacity

- [ ] Add releases
  - Backend: create `ReleaseModel` with version, name, status, targetDate, releasedAt, project, workspace
  - Backend: add optional `release` reference to `TaskModel`
  - API: CRUD releases, assign tasks, generate release notes from completed tasks
  - Analytics: release completion, blockers, overdue tasks

- [ ] Add milestones
  - Backend: create `MilestoneModel` with name, description, dueDate, project, workspace, status
  - Backend: link tasks and epics to milestones
  - API: milestone progress and overdue risk

- [ ] Add team capacity planning
  - Backend: create `CapacityModel` per sprint/member with availableHours and plannedStoryPoints
  - Analytics: planned vs completed story points, logged hours, over-allocation
  - Rules: warn when assigned work exceeds member capacity

## Phase 4 - Engineering Metrics

